Package: libspandsp2
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         ${shlibs:Depends}
Multi-Arch: same
Description: Telephony signal processing library
 spandsp is a low-level signal processing library that modulates and
 demodulates signals commonly used in telephony, such as the "noise"
  generated by a fax modem or DTMF touchpad.
 .
 This package contains the shared library.

Package: libspandsp-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: libspandsp2 (= ${binary:Version}),
         libtiff-dev | libtiff5-dev,
         ${misc:Depends}
Breaks: libspandsp-doc (<< 0.0.6+dfsg+snap20180108)
Replaces: libspandsp-doc (<< 0.0.6+dfsg+snap20180108)
Multi-Arch: same
Description: Telephony signal processing library - development headers
 spandsp is a low-level signal processing library that modulates and
 demodulates signals commonly used in telephony, such as the "noise"
 generated by a fax modem or DTMF touchpad.
 .
 This package contains the static library and development headers.

